From: 3090 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-05-08
Subject: [PATCH] gemma4_mm: support per-expert AWQ source format (mirror gemma4_causal)

Closes 21B-REAP rebuild + Gemma 4 26B HF mirror compatibility issues
(both surfaced in 3090 README "Suggested next" 2026-05-04). Upstream
v0.5.11 gemma4_mm.py only supports HF transformers' fused-experts source
format (experts.gate_up_proj [E, 2*I, H], one tensor per layer) — but
llmcompressor-saved AWQ checkpoints (mattbucci/gemma-4-26B-AWQ,
gemma-4-21b-REAP-AWQ-thinking-vision-v2, etc.) ship per-expert keys like
experts.<i>.gate_proj.qweight / qzeros / scales.

Result: 3090's gemma4_mm.py loader silently fails to find the per-expert
weights → vision tower stays at random init (validator passes round/circle
keyword grep but model hallucinates content), or the entire MoE block
stays uninit → 0/3 PASS on the gemma-4-21b-REAP-AWQ-thinking-vision-v2.

R9700's gemma4_causal.py at python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_causal.py:920+
already handles BOTH formats via a two-tier mapping (per-expert via
FusedMoE.make_expert_params_mapping + fused via the hand-built mapping).
This is the symmetric port for the gemma4_mm.py multimodal loader.

After patch:
- llmcompressor per-expert AWQ source (experts.0.gate_proj.qweight) →
  loaded into experts.w13_qweight shard "w1" expert 0 via FusedMoE
  weight_loader (handles awq_marlin runtime conversion).
- HF transformers fused source (experts.gate_up_proj [E, 2I, H]) →
  unchanged path, still chunks gate/up internally.

Note on testing: dev rig is on TP=1 / 24 GB which is too tight for Gemma 4
26B + KV cache; full TP=2 verification deferred to second-card return.
Static apply check + ast.parse() verified clean against fresh v0.5.11
worktree. Patch is symmetric to R9700's already-validated
gemma4_causal.py implementation.

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_mm.py b/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_mm.py
--- a/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_mm.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_mm.py
@@ -32,6 +32,7 @@ from sglang.srt.layers.attention.triton_backend import TritonAttnBackend
 from sglang.srt.layers.layernorm import Gemma4RMSNorm
 from sglang.srt.layers.linear import ReplicatedLinear
 from sglang.srt.layers.logits_processor import LogitsProcessor
+from sglang.srt.layers.moe.fused_moe_triton.layer import FusedMoE
 from sglang.srt.layers.quantization.base_config import QuantizationConfig
 from sglang.srt.managers.mm_utils import (
     MultiModalityDataPaddingPatternMultimodalTokens,
@@ -714,7 +715,28 @@ class Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration(PreTrainedModel):
         k_eq_v_layers = self._get_k_eq_v_layers()

         num_experts = getattr(self.config.text_config, "num_experts", 0) or 0
-        expert_params_mapping = [
+
+        # Per-expert mapping for AWQ/GPTQ checkpoints saved by llmcompressor
+        # (experts.<i>.gate_proj.qweight / qzeros / scales).  Mirrors the
+        # dual-format support already present in gemma4_causal.py; closes
+        # 3090 Suggested-next entries for 21B-REAP rebuild + gemma-4-26B-AWQ
+        # HF mirror format mismatch.  Returns tuples of (param_name,
+        # weight_name, expert_id, shard_id) where weight_name is e.g.
+        # "experts.0.gate_proj.".
+        per_expert_params_mapping = (
+            FusedMoE.make_expert_params_mapping(
+                ckpt_gate_proj_name="gate_proj",
+                ckpt_down_proj_name="down_proj",
+                ckpt_up_proj_name="up_proj",
+                num_experts=num_experts,
+            )
+            if num_experts > 0
+            else []
+        )
+
+        # Fused mapping for BF16 HF-transformers checkpoints
+        # (experts.gate_up_proj [E, 2*I, H], one tensor per layer).
+        fused_expert_params_mapping = [
             # (param_name, ckpt_weight_name, shard_ids)
             # gate_up_proj is fused [E, 2*I, H] — chunk into w1 (gate) + w3 (up)
             ("experts.w13_weight", "experts.gate_up_proj", ("w1", "w3")),
@@ -767,10 +789,34 @@ class Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration(PreTrainedModel):
                 and int(m.group(1)) in k_eq_v_layers
             )

-            # MoE expert weights checked first (gate_up_proj contains "up_proj"
-            # which would false-match the stacked dense MLP mapping).
             orig_name = name
-            for param_name, weight_name, shard_ids in expert_params_mapping:
+
+            # --- Per-expert AWQ/GPTQ weights (experts.<i>.gate_proj.qweight) ---
+            # Checked first so the per-expert format takes precedence over the
+            # fused format and the stacked dense MLP mapping.
+            is_expert_weight = False
+            for param_name, weight_name, expert_id, shard_id in per_expert_params_mapping:
+                if weight_name not in name:
+                    continue
+                is_expert_weight = True
+                name = name.replace(weight_name, param_name)
+                if name not in params_dict:
+                    continue
+                param = params_dict[name]
+                weight_loader = param.weight_loader
+                weight_loader(
+                    param, loaded_weight, name,
+                    shard_id=shard_id, expert_id=expert_id,
+                )
+                loaded_params.add(name)
+                break
+            if is_expert_weight:
+                continue
+
+            # --- Fused BF16 experts (experts.gate_up_proj [E, 2*I, H]) ---
+            # MoE expert weights checked next (gate_up_proj contains "up_proj"
+            # which would false-match the stacked dense MLP mapping).
+            for param_name, weight_name, shard_ids in fused_expert_params_mapping:
                 name = orig_name
                 if weight_name not in name:
                     continue
